  abstract = {This document articulates our professional learning theory of change which puts focus squarely on student learning. By design, a theory of change does not and cannot focus on each and every possible impact of professional learning. Instead, the theory of change included here focuses on the key levers activated by effective professional learning that drive instructional improvement. Specifically, this theory of change connects the following elements: - Effective and classroom-relevant professional learning - The knowledge and skills that help teachers turn learning evidence into instructional action - Measures of the impact of that professional learning In detailing these connections, the theory of change looks to illuminate a model for high-quality practice that guides NWEA professional learning in its commitment to partnering to help all kids learn.},
